::document
id: init
authority: governing
applies-to: claude-code
read: every-session | before-any-action
version: v0.1.0
audit_round: r0
versioning_tier: full
purpose: project-level governance overlay — extends or overrides ~/.aeleon/global/init.aeml

  This file carries project-specific governance: the project's name, root path, orientation,
  phases, session-close obligations, and any per-project overrides of the kernel's universal rules.

  The kernel's universal rules live at ~/.aeleon/global/init.aeml and are read first.
  Anything declared here takes precedence over the kernel's defaults.


::project
name: fumage
root: ~/projects/fumage
handover-dir: ~/projects/fumage/handover/
memory-entry: ~/.claude/projects/-Users-scottreisinger/memory/project-fumage.md
::end-project


::orientation

  Fumage is a men's fragrance reference site — catalog, editorial guides, dupe browser,
  notes library, and wardrobe system — targeting beginners through serious collectors.
  The design aesthetic is apothecary-editorial: dark (#0c0906 background), warm amber
  accents, serif typography. Built on Next.js, Prisma, PostgreSQL via Supabase, Meilisearch
  for search, deployed to Vercel with auto-deploy on push to main.

  Current scale: 685 fragrances, 159 houses, 358 notes, 23 dupes, 1542 similar pairs.
  21 guide articles live. TypeScript zero-error policy is maintained at all times.

::end-orientation


::phases

  ::phase
  id: 1
  name: foundation
  status: complete
  ::end-phase
  # Schema migrated, database seeded, auth wired. Completed 2026-04-24.

  ::phase
  id: 2
  name: app-router
  status: complete
  ::end-phase
  # All routed pages built. Completed 2026-04-24.

  ::phase
  id: 3
  name: search
  status: complete
  ::end-phase
  # Meilisearch integrated. Completed 2026-04-24.

  ::phase
  id: 4
  name: launch
  status: active
  ::end-phase
  # Vercel deploy live at fumage.vercel.app. Custom domain (ai-009) outstanding.

::end-phases


::session-close
sequence: ordered
obligation: mandatory — a session that ends without completing all steps is incomplete

  step[1] Verify TypeScript compiles clean: run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Resolve any errors before proceeding.
  step[2] Push all commits to origin: run `git push`. Confirm push succeeded before writing the handover.
  step[3] Write the handover file to ./handover/ using the filename format
          claude-session-handover-{YYYYMMDDTHHmmssZ}.aeml where the timestamp is derived
          from the system clock at the moment of writing. The git state section must reflect
          post-push reality: branch name, clean/dirty state, and latest commit hash only.
          Never record "ahead of origin by N commits" as a final state.
  step[4] Update the project memory entry at
          ~/.claude/projects/-Users-scottreisinger/memory/project-fumage.md
          with the new session number and the exact filename of the handover just written.

::end-session-close


::design-constants

  background:       #0c0906
  body-text:        stone-200
  accent:           amber-500 / amber-400
  card-border:      border-stone-800, hover border-stone-600
  label-style:      text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]
  aesthetic:        apothecary-editorial — dark, warm, not sterile e-commerce

  guide-articles:
    container:      max-w-2xl
    typography:     font-serif display and body
    pull-quotes:    left amber border
    components:     PullQuote, SectionLabel, FragLinks, FragCard — defined inline per file (intentionally not shared)

  nav-order:        Catalog · Houses · Notes · Dupes · Guide · Search · Wardrobe/Sign in
  mobile-nav:       MobileNav.tsx (client component); desktop nav is hidden md:flex in Nav.tsx

::end-design-constants


::slug-discipline

  rule: always verify fragrance slugs against prisma/data/fragrance_database.json using the id field
        before referencing them in guide articles. never invent a slug. render unmatched references
        as plain text or pills, never as broken links.

::end-slug-discipline


::commit-discipline

  rule: one commit per discrete feature or article. imperative subject line. Co-Authored-By trailer on every commit.
  rule: never commit with TypeScript errors present.

::end-commit-discipline


::project-overrides

  # No kernel rule overrides at this time. Kernel rules apply in full.

::end-project-overrides

::end-document
